parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission range sensor can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or jerk when shifting gears, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
the vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power
the transmission slips into neutral
the vehicle shakes or lurches
the odometer scrambles or displays incorrect information.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TCM can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
the transmission slips into neutral
the vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
the check engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Body and Throttle Position Sensor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body and throttle position sensor can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or jerk when shifting gears, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
the vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power
the engine light comes on and the vehicle goes into limp mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper arm can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The windshield wiper arm comes off while driving
reducing visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the deactivation of the passenger airbag, potentially causing injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident. Additionally, the faulty airbag system can cause the airbag warning light to stay on, creating a distraction for the driver and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on
the passenger airbag is deactivated
the airbag module displays an internal fault code
the airbag system fails to detect the presence of a passenger
the airbag system displays a false warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. Additionally, the faulty transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, creating a hazardous situation on the road.
symptoms: The vehicle has trouble accelerating from a stop
the check engine light comes on
the transmission displays a "clunk" or "scrambled gear" display on the dashboard
the vehicle hesitates or stalls
the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical fire under the steering column can cause damage to the vehicle's electrical system, potentially leading to a loss of vehicle control, injury, or even death.
symptoms: Sudden and unexplained fire under the steering column
smoke or burning smell from the dashboard or steering column area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission sensor can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to difficulty shifting gears, slow acceleration, and reduced vehicle performance, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Difficulty shifting into gear
slow acceleration
restricted driving
transmission slipping or hesitation
error codes on the auto scanner indicating a transmission sensor fault.
